                <p><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/games/doom-the-dark-ages/" data-ref-id="5000-631964">Doom: The Dark Ages</a> is getting a food promotion, and it's neither Mountain Dew nor Doritos: Xbox has announced that it has partnered with Prince St. Pizza to offer a Doom-inspired pizza that comes with some digital goods.</p><p><a href="https://princestreetpizza.com/" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Prince St. Pizza</a>, a pizzeria chain with a handful of locations in the US and Canada, is selling <a href="https://news.xbox.com/en-us/2025/05/12/delivery-from-hell-xbox-doom-team-up-prince-st-pizza/" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">"Hellfire Pepperoni,"</a> a pie emphasizing spicy ingredients that supposedly evoke the fire and brimstone of Doom's setting. This pizza includes pepperoni, spicy sauce, habanero peppers, and hot honey, and it comes in Sicilian style (thick, square crust with crispy edges).</p>



    
