<p>Purchasers of the Hellfire Pepperoni will also get some digital goodies thrown in. You'll get a timed-exclusive, in-game skin for the Doomslayer alongside a code for a one-month trial of Game Pass. Apparently Prince St. Pizza will also serve the pizza in a custom box, if you order takeout.</p><p>If you happen to grab a pizza and get the in-game skin, you'll be able to use it when Doom: The Dark Ages launches later this week, on May 15. This isn't the most outrageous tie-in that Microsoft has announced for the game, either: Last week, the company showed off <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/this-custom-doom-harley-is-a-sight-to-behold/1100-6531325/" data-ref-id="1100-6531325">a custom Harley Davidson decked out in Doom decals and flair</a>. Microsoft is offering <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/doom-the-dark-ages-preorders-deals-bonuses-bundles-and-more/1100-6528996/" data-ref-id="1100-6528996">a good number of different bundles and preorder bonuses</a>, and you can pick up <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/doom-the-dark-ages-xbox-wireless-controller-game-bundle-deals-amazon-walmart/1100-6530902/" data-ref-id="1100-6530902">a special Doom: The Dark Ages Xbox controller</a>, if that's your thing. Be sure to check out <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/doom-the-dark-ages-launch-times-and-preload-details-revealed/1100-6531435/" data-ref-id="1100-6531435">all the details about preload requirements and launch times here</a>. In our review, <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/reviews/doom-the-dark-ages-review/1900-6418361/" data-ref-id="1900-6418361">GameSpot gave Doom: The Dark Ages an 8/10</a>, praising its battlefield design and new weaponry. </p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
